The newly sworn Anambra Governor Charles Soludo, has apologised for the disruption at his inauguration on Thursday. The disruption followed the fracas between wife of his predecessor, Ebelechukwu Obiano and late Dim Chukwuemeka Odumegwu Ojukwu’s wife Bianca, who engaged in a free-for-all. In a statement Thursday after the inauguration from Soludo’s media office by it’s head, Joe Anatune, Soludo apologised for the breach of protocol.   BREAKING: Akpanudoedehe absent as Buni, Sani Bello, CECPC…     Job loss: Reps move to save Garki Hospital’s staff     BREAKING: OAU appoints Prof Bamire as new Vice-Chancellor   “The breach was caused by improper communication which itself arose from a personal issue between the two parties involved in the breach. ” Steps are being taken to resolve the misunderstanding and restore the parties to their previous relationship. “Anambra State has over the years been known for a huge stock of social harmony, and the stock will increase substantially in the years ahead as part of the concerted effort to accelerate the state’s development,” the statement reads.